&lt;p&gt;JJob Summary&lt;br&gt;Join a mission-critical flight test team supporting the U.S. Air Force&#39;s operational test and evaluation activities. As an Instrumentation Technician, you will play a hands-on role in keeping advanced airborne data acquisition systems mission-ready for daily test sorties on fighter aircraft. Working directly on the flight line, you will perform preflight inspections, configure data recorders, recover postflight media, and troubleshoot instrumentation issues.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;Daily Test Mission Support – Preflight&lt;br&gt;• Coordinate test aircraft access with squadron maintenance teams.&lt;br&gt;• Conduct visual inspections of the data acquisition system and associated harnesses.&lt;br&gt;• Load media into data recorders and verify proper mounting.&lt;br&gt;• Confirm data recorder bus link status is active and ready for flight.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Daily Test Mission Support – Postflight&lt;br&gt;• Recover recorded media from aircraft and deliver it to the data processing team.&lt;br&gt;• Ensure the data system is properly powered down after each sortie.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Data System Maintenance&lt;br&gt;• Notify the Operations Engineer of anomalies identified during debriefs or post-flight inspections.&lt;br&gt;• Perform corrective actions on open issues per Operations Engineer disposition.&lt;br&gt;• Maintain accurate records of system status, modifications, and repairs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Logistics &amp;amp; Lab Support&lt;br&gt;• Provide support for instrumentation logistics activities (parts, shipments, inventory).&lt;br&gt;• Support lab operations, including bench testing, configuration, and equipment preparation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• U.S. Citizenship with an active Top Secret (TS/SCI) DoD security clearance, eligible for Special Access Program (SAP) read-in.&lt;br&gt;• Technical background in electronics, avionics, instrumentation, or a closely related field.&lt;br&gt;• Ability to interpret technical drawings, schematics, and system specifications.&lt;br&gt;• Strong attention to detail and disciplined documentation practices.&lt;br&gt;• Ability to work on the flight line in an outdoor environment, including occasional lifting and extended periods standing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Preferred Qualifications / Desired Skills&lt;br&gt;• Hands-on experience with USAF flight test instrumentation on platforms such as F-35, F-22, F-15E, or F-16.&lt;br&gt;• Working knowledge of military maintenance systems such as the Integrated Maintenance Data System (IMDS).&lt;br&gt;• Experience with bus-based data acquisition systems (e.g., MIL-STD-1553, ARINC 429, Ethernet-based telemetry).&lt;br&gt;• Demonstrates initiative, sound judgment, and strong communication skills when coordinating across maintenance, engineering, and operations teams.&lt;br&gt;• Comfortable working in a secure, mission-driven environment with shifting priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
